      <abstract abstract-type="teaser" id="abs0020">
        <p>ADGRL1 encodes an adhesion G protein-coupled receptor implicated in synaptic development and activity. We conducted clinical and biochemical studies in humans with <italic>ADGRL1</italic> variants and behavioral and cellular studies in <italic>Adgrl1</italic> null mice. Our findings demonstrate that <italic>ADGRL1</italic> haploinsufficiency leads to consistent developmental, neurological, and behavioral abnormalities in mice and humans.</p>
